# Copy this file to '.env' and make desired changes

# DC_IMAGE=ghcr.io/dealer-s-choice/dealers_choice:latest

# Published (host) port. Also names the log files written under DC_OUTPUT_DIR:
#   hands-<DC_PORT>.txt and results-<DC_PORT>.md
# so you can run two servers (e.g. 22777 and 22778) without their logs colliding.
# DC_PORT=22777

# Extra server args (the --log-hands/--log-game-results paths are already set for
# you, named by DC_PORT). Use this for things like --conf, --verbose, --name.
# DC_EXTRA_ARGS=--conf /dc_config/server.conf --name "My Table"

# Storage. Leave DC_*_DIR unset (the default) to use managed named volumes —
# owned by the container's non-root user, so it just works with no uid setup.
# Set a DC_*_DIR to a host PATH to bind-mount instead (read logs on the host,
# serve servers.json from a website, etc.); see DC_UID below for that case.
# DC_CONFIG_DIR=/home/.../.config/dealers-choice       # /dc_config (server.conf)
# DC_OUTPUT_DIR=/home/.../.local/state/dealers-choice  # /dc_output (logs)

# DC_PASSWORD=

# Docker network mode for the server + registry. Default "bridge" (uses the
# published ports). Set to "host" ONLY on a host whose public IP is on its own
# NIC (a plain VPS, e.g. BitFolk): bridge there makes a co-located server's
# announce reach the registry from the docker gateway (172.x) instead of the
# public IP, so it gets mis-listed. Leave it unset where the cloud NATs the
# public IP externally (e.g. Oracle/OCI) -- bridge works and keeps isolation.
# DC_NET_MODE=host

# Only needed when you point a DC_*_DIR at a HOST path (bind mount): the container
# runs unprivileged, so its uid/gid must own that path. Set these to the owner
# (`id -u` / `id -g`) and chown the dir once: sudo chown -R <uid>:<gid> <dir>.
# Named volumes (the default) need none of this.
# DC_UID=1000
# DC_GID=1000

# Bot service — only used by: docker compose --profile bot up
# Connects to DC_BOT_HOST:DC_BOT_PORT. Defaults point at the in-compose server
# service (dealers-choice-server on DC_PORT); set them to reach an external server.
# The bot has no depends_on, so start a server yourself or point it elsewhere.
# DC_BOT_HOST=dealers-choice-server
# DC_BOT_PORT defaults to DC_PORT, so reusing a per-instance env file points the
# bot at that instance's server. Set it only to target a different server.
# DC_BOT_PORT=22777
# DC_BOT_ARGS=--verbose

# Registry (directory) service — only used by: docker compose --profile registry up
# DC_REGISTRY_DIR=/home/.../.local/share/dealers-choice/registry
# DC_REGISTRY_PORT=22070
# DC_REGISTRY_ARGS=--verbose
